[SN]TITLE[SN]
Diners evacuated after Dundee restaurant blaze

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Diners were forced to evacuate an Indian restaurant in Dundee after a fire broke out.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The blaze started in the ground-floor kitchen of the Mint Indian tapas bar and restaurant in Perth Road and travelled through the extraction unit.
Staff raised the alarm just before 19:00 on Friday, and diners were taken to safety before the emergency services arrived at the scene.
Four appliances attended and the fire was extinguished about an hour later.
